    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <div class="date">Effective Date: April 1, 2026 · Last Updated: April 1, 2026</div>
  </div>

  <p>Sisterhood(verb) ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use the Sisterhood(verb) community app and website (collectively, the "Service"). By using our Service, you agree to the practices described in this policy.</p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p><strong>Information you provide directly:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Account information: name, email address, and password when you create an account</li>
    <li>Profile information: display name, bio, location, and profile and banner photos you choose to upload</li>
    <li>Content you create: posts, replies, and other content you share in the community</li>
    <li>Communications: messages you send to us and event registrations</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Information collected automatically:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Usage data: which features you use, circles you join, and how you interact with the app</li>
    <li>Device information: browser type, operating system, and device type</li>
    <li>Authentication tokens: to keep you securely logged in</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Create and manage your account</li>
    <li>Provide and improve the Sisterhood(verb) community experience</li>
    <li>Send you community emails, announcements, and updates you've opted into</li>
    <li>Respond to your questions and support requests</li>
    <li>Ensure the safety and integrity of our community</li>
    <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do not sell your personal information to third parties. Ever.</p>

  <h2>3. How We Share Your Information</h2>
  <p>Your profile information (name, bio, profile photo) is visible to other members of the Sisterhood(verb) community. Your posts and replies are visible to other members within the app.</p>
  <p>We share information with the following trusted service providers who help us operate the Service:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Supabase</strong> — database and authentication (supabase.com)</li>
    <li><strong>Resend</strong> — transactional email delivery (resend.com)</li>
    <li><strong>Vercel</strong> — hosting and infrastructure (vercel.com)</li>
    <li><strong>GIPHY</strong> — GIF search functionality (giphy.com)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>These providers are contractually obligated to protect your information and may only use it to provide services to us.</p>
  <p>We may disclose your information if required by law, or if we believe disclosure is necessary to protect the rights, safety, or property of Sisterhood(verb), our members, or others.</p>

  <h2>4. Data Storage and Security</h2>
  <p>Your data is stored securely through Supabase, which uses industry-standard encryption and security practices. We use row-level security policies to ensure members can only access their own data. Profile photos and banners are stored in secure cloud storage.</p>
  <p>While we take reasonable steps to protect your information, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure. We encourage you to use a strong, unique password for your account.</p>

  <h2>5. Your Choices and Rights</h2>
  <p>You have the following rights regarding your personal information:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Access:</strong> You can view and update your profile information at any time within the app</li>
    <li><strong>Correction:</strong> You can edit your profile information directly in your account settings</li>
    <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> You can request deletion of your account and associated data by contacting us at sisterhoodverb@gmail.com</li>
    <li><strong>Opt-out:</strong> You can opt out of community emails by contacting us directly</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>Sisterhood(verb) is intended for women 18 years of age and older. We do not knowingly collect personal information from anyone under 18. If you believe a minor has created an account, please contact us immediately at sisterhoodverb@gmail.com and we will delete the account.</p>

  <h2>7. Community Content</h2>
  <p>Content you post in the Sisterhood(verb) community — including text posts, replies, and shared media — is visible to other members of the platform. Please be thoughtful about what personal information you choose to share publicly within the community. Our Community Agreements require all members to respect the privacy and confidentiality of what is shared in this space.</p>

  <h2>8. Cookies and Local Storage</h2>
  <p>We use browser local storage to remember your login session and preferences (such as whether you have completed onboarding). We do not use third-party advertising cookies. You can clear local storage at any time through your browser settings, though this will log you out of the app.</p>

  <h2>9. Third-Party Links</h2>
  <p>Our Service may contain links to third-party websites or services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of those third parties. We encourage you to review their privacy policies before providing any personal information.</p>

  <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make significant changes, we will notify members through the app or via email. Your continued use of the Service after changes become effective constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

  <h2>11. California Privacy Rights</h2>
  <p>If you are a California resident, you have the right to know what personal information we collect, disclose, or sell about you. As stated in this policy, we do not sell personal information. You may contact us at sisterhoodverb@gmail.com to exercise your rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA).</p>

